    "dialogue": [
        {
            "n": 0,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "Hi everybody.\nToday we will talk about the Aeternum.",
            "next": 2
        },
        {
        },
        {
            "n": 2,
            "type": "choice",
            "text": "Does somebody know what it is?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "text": "I do, ma'am!",
                    "next": 3
                },
                {
                    "text": "...",
                    "next": 5
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "n": 3,
            "type": "playerline",
            "text": "It's a machine that makes people\nlive forever.",
            "next": 4
        },
        {
            "n": 4,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "Yes, that's right, John.",
            "next": 7
        },
        {
            "n": 5,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "Nobody knows?",
            "next": 6
        },
        {
            "n": 6,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "It is the machine that made eternal\nlife possible.",
            "next": 10
        },
        {
            "n": 7,
            "type": "choice",
            "text": "John, do you know how it works?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "text": "Yes I do",
                    "next": 8
                },
                {
                    "text": "No",
                    "next": 10
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "n": 8,
            "type": "playerline",
            "text": "Rich people take the life of poor\npeople, my father says.",
            "next": 9
        },
        {
            "n": 9,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "Well, this is not the truth.\nNot exactly.",
            "next": 10
        },
        {
            "n": 10,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "Bad people are sacrificed so that\ngood people can live.",
            "next": 11
        },
        {
            "n": 11,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "For example criminals lose the right\nto live,",
            "next": 12
        },
        {
            "n": 12,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "and people who make a better society\ncan take their vital energy.",
            "next": 13
        },
        {
            "n": 13,
            "type": "choice",
            "text": "",
            "options": [
                {
                    "text": "My father said...",
                    "next": 14
                },
                {
                    "text": "...",
                    "next": 16
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "n": 14,
            "type": "playerline",
            "text": "My father said lives can be sold for\nmoney, or lost due to debts.",
            "next": 15
        },
        {
            "n": 15,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "Yes, that's right.",
            "next": 16
        },
        {
            "n": 16,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "The United States are ahead of the\nrest of the world,",
            "next": 17
        },
        {
            "n": 17,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "it's the only place where people with\nmerit get the long life they deserve",
            "next": 18
        },
        {
            "n": 18,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "and junkies and weak people don't\ndeserve to live.",
            "next": 19
        },
        {
            "n": 19,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "But we all have rights. If you have\nlost your life and it has not yet",
            "next": 20
        },
        {
            "n": 20,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "been used by its owner, you have the\nright to buy it back.",
            "next": 22
        },
        {
        },
        {
            "n": 22,
            "type": "choice",
            "text": "",
            "options": [
                {
                    "text": "What about the children?",
                    "next": 23
                },
                {
                    "text": "...",
                    "next": 27
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "n": 23,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "You belong to your parents, or\nwhoever they sell your life to,",
            "next": 24
        },
        {
            "n": 24,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "until the age of 16 when you can buy\nyour life to its owner.",
            "next": 25
        },
        {
            "n": 25,
            "type": "choice",
            "text": "",
            "options": [
                {
                    "text": "It's unfair!",
                    "next": 26
                },
                {
                    "text": "...",
                    "next": 27
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "n": 26,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "Children don't have the maturity to\ndecide what to do with their lives.",
            "next": 27
        },
        {
            "n": 27,
            "type": "npcline",
            "text": "Now, the lesson is over.\nSee you tomorrow!",
            "next": 28
        },
        {
            "n": 28,
